The paper focuses on network embedding, which is a subfield of machine learning and data mining. The use of adversarial training methods is a popular technique in deep learning, which falls under the category of large-scale machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the issue of noisy information in real-world networks, which is a common problem in social network analysis (cs.SI) and network science (cs.SD). Additionally, the paper proposes a new regularization method for network embedding, which is a subfield of network science (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
